revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{Uses TemplateStyles|Template:Skip to top and bottom/styles.css}}
The template isn't empty, it produces '''two arrow icons in the bottom right corner'''.

==Usage==
Can be placed on [[WP:GOVPS|administration pages]] (not-articles) when appropriate. This usually means pages in the "Wikipedia:" and "Help:" namespaces, but sometime also exist on user pages.

This template produces 2 icons on the bottom-right corner. Clicking the rightmost one takes you to the bottom of the page while clicking on the left one takes you to the top of the page. To use this template just put the following anywhere on the page:

{{tlx|Skip to top and bottom}}

==Example==
<code><nowiki>{{Skip to top and bottom}}</nowiki></code> shall produce what you see in the bottom-right corner.

Registered users can hide the icons by placing this in {{yourcss}}:
<syntaxhighlight lang="css">#skip-to-top-button, #skip-to-bottom-button {display: none;}</syntaxhighlight>

{{skip templates}}

<includeonly>{{Sandbox other||
<!-- CATEGORIES BELOW THIS LINE, PLEASE: -->
[[Category:Help namespace templates]]
}}</includeonly>

